## ‚ö†Ô∏è Common Pitfalls

### Pitfall 1: Over-Engineering Simple Problems
{% raw %}
```javascript
// ‚ùå WRONG: Over-engineered solution
const add = curry((a, b) => a + b);
const result = add(5)(3);

// ‚úÖ CORRECT: Simple solution
const add = (a, b) => a + b;
const result = add(5, 3);
```
{% endraw %}

### Pitfall 2: Ignoring Performance
{% raw %}
```javascript
// ‚ùå WRONG: Creating new arrays in loops
const processArray = (arr) => {
    let result = [];
    for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
        result = [...result, arr[i] * 2]; // Creates new array each iteration
    }
    return result;
};

// ‚úÖ CORRECT: Efficient approach
const processArray = (arr) => arr.map(x => x * 2);
```
{% endraw %}

### Pitfall 3: Forgetting Error Handling
{% raw %}
```javascript
// ‚ùå WRONG: No error handling
const divide = (a, b) => a / b;

// ‚úÖ CORRECT: With error handling
const divide = (a, b) => {
    if (b === 0) throw new Error("Division by zero");
    return a / b;
};
```
